7
8 SECTION 1. INTENT OF AMENDMENT. It is the intent of this amendment to
9 the Arkansas Constitution to protect the right to keep and bear arms
10 guaranteed under the Arkansas Constitution.
11
12 SECTION 2. Arkansas Constitution, Article 2, § 5, is amended to read
13 as follows:
14 § 5. Right to keep and bear arms.
15 (a) The citizens of this State shall have the right to keep and bear
16 arms, for:
17 (1) their Their common defense;
18 (2) Lawful hunting and recreational use; and
19 (3) Any other lawful purpose.
20 (b) The right to keep and bear arms under subsection (a) of this
21 section includes without limitation the possession and use of:
22 (1) Ammunition;
23 (2) Firearm accessories; and
24 (3) Firearm components.
25 (c) The right to keep and bear arms under subsection (a) of this
26 section is a natural, fundamental, and individual right that shall not be
27 infringed.
28
29 SECTION 3. EFFECTIVE DATE. This amendment to the Arkansas
30 Constitution is effective on and after January 1, 2027.
